place.name: SCO RUSTON
place.gazetteerText: RUSTON (South), or Sco-Ruston, a parish in Tunstead district, Norfolk; near the North Walsham railway, 2 miles N E of Coltishall. Post-town, Coltishall, under Norwich. Acres, 471. Real property, £1,033. Pop., 102. Houses, 27. The living is a p. curacy, annexed to Tunstead, in the diocese of Norwich. The church is ancient. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
